	From the tree\'92s perch, I observe the pine-topped island across the water, a gigantic ferry slowly moving away from shore, the miniscule person reading on the beach. The relationships between these objects produce a sense of space and perhaps quietude. They are less tangible in the moment, but I know that with some effort I could proceed towards them, albeit with some considerable effort. Yet, during and by journey\'92s end, my perspective on them will have changed. In my office, the scale of the space and my conception of it circumscribes that kind of physical possibility. Yet, as it does so, the possibilities for heightened attention and exploration of the objects in the room become more possible. These choices of space and perspective then become generative of the perceptions and conceptions that are produced from them.\
